00:58:48.420 --> 00:58:52.180
I actually have to collaborate with other
artists and with other writers.

00:58:52.180 --> 00:58:56.630
Then when I write books for my other publisher,
1st, 2nd Books, most of those are stand alone

00:58:56.630 --> 00:58:57.630
graphic novels.

00:58:57.630 --> 00:59:00.820
They're a story with a beginning, middle,
and end.

00:59:00.820 --> 00:59:04.040
For those, I generally just have ideas on
my own.

00:59:04.040 --> 00:59:08.030
Sometimes I'll work with a partner, but often
they'll start off as just in my own head.

00:59:08.030 --> 00:59:13.190
All right, that sounds like a question from
somebody who might be wondering where ideas

00:59:13.190 --> 00:59:14.190
come from.

00:59:14.190 --> 00:59:15.190
Is that true for you?

00:59:15.190 --> 00:59:16.190
Okay.

00:59:16.190 --> 00:59:18.880
So, I get this question a lot.

00:59:18.880 --> 00:59:21.900
Kids will sometimes ask me where my ideas
come from.

00:59:21.900 --> 00:59:24.700
Often, my ideas come from my own life.

00:59:24.700 --> 00:59:28.900
Sometimes, if you feel like you have a creative
assignment and you don't have any ideas for

00:59:28.900 --> 00:59:31.230
it, just think about your own life.

00:59:31.230 --> 00:59:34.650
Even if your own life seems boring, I guarantee
if you think about it long enough, it is not.

00:59:34.650 --> 00:59:39.400
