I guarantee you, ideas are gonna come out.

01:00:02.360 --> 01:00:05.060
CARLA: I need that now.

01:00:05.060 --> 01:00:06.060
GENE: Yes?

01:00:06.060 --> 01:00:10.440
AUDIENCE: How did you feel when you released
your first book?

01:00:10.440 --> 01:00:13.600
GENE: How did I feel?

01:00:13.600 --> 01:00:17.560
The very first book that I released was in
fifth grade.

01:00:17.560 --> 01:00:18.560
It was amazing.

01:00:18.560 --> 01:00:20.860
AUDIENCE: When you were a grown up?

01:00:20.860 --> 01:00:25.690
GENE: As a grown up, the first book that I
released was Gordon Yamamoto and the King

01:00:25.690 --> 01:00:26.690
of the Geeks.

01:00:26.690 --> 01:00:29.350
I actually self-published that, so I didn't
even go through a publisher.

01:00:29.350 --> 01:00:34.240
I just got it printed up myself and I'd try
to go to stores and local comic book conventions

01:00:34.240 --> 01:00:36.370
to sell it by hand.

01:00:36.370 --> 01:00:37.370
It was great.

01:00:37.370 --> 01:00:38.370
It was a lot of work.

01:00:38.370 --> 01:00:43.550
It's a lot of work to publish your own comic,
