01:02:50.560 --> 01:02:53.560
AUDIENCE: What materials do you use to make
your comics?

01:02:53.560 --> 01:02:54.740
GENE: I'm sorry, what was that?

01:02:54.740 --> 01:02:56.940
AUDIENCE: What materials do you use-
GENE: What materials?

01:02:56.940 --> 01:02:57.940
That's great.

01:02:57.940 --> 01:03:04.420
So, when I was your age, I read this book
called How to Make Comics the Marvel Way.

01:03:04.420 --> 01:03:08.580
It was written by Stan Lee and Stan Lee told
me I had to use a certain set of materials.

01:03:08.580 --> 01:03:14.930
Told me I had to use Bristol board, which
is like this super thick, white paper.

01:03:14.930 --> 01:03:16.480
Really, really thick.

01:03:16.480 --> 01:03:19.030
He told me I had to use a certain kind of
pencil.

01:03:19.030 --> 01:03:23.830
He told me I had to use a brush and a bottle
of ink.

01:03:23.830 --> 01:03:26.910
So I did; that's how I started off making
comics.

01:03:26.910 --> 01:03:30.400
Then after I became an adult.

01:03:30.400 --> 01:03:34.500
After I started going to conventions and hanging
out with other cartoonists, I realized that

01:03:34.500 --> 01:03:37.650
not everybody makes comics the Marvel way.

01:03:37.650 --> 01:03:42.220
Almost every cartoonist you talk to, they
will have figured out their own set of materials.

01:03:42.220 --> 01:03:46.190
So, if you want to make comics, if you want
to make are in general, you should experiment.

01:03:46.190 --> 01:03:49.650
You should figure out what materials feel
best for you.

01:03:49.650 --> 01:03:53.690
Right now, I am using a regular number two
pencil to draw.

01:03:53.690 --> 01:03:56.800
I'm using what's called a "blue pencil" to
do my sketching.

01:03:56.800 --> 01:04:01.820
It's a certain shade of blue called "non-photo
blue" and I no longer ink with a brush and

01:04:01.820 --> 01:04:02.820
a bottle of ink.

01:04:02.820 --> 01:04:04.800
I actually ink with a Japanese brush pen.

01:04:04.800 --> 01:04:05.990
I don't need that bottle of ink anymore.

01:04:05.990 --> 01:04:06.990
Yes?

01:04:06.990 --> 01:04:07.990
Young lady with the headband?

01:04:07.990 --> 01:04:15.020
AUDIENCE: What is your Chinese name?

01:04:15.020 --> 01:04:17.630
GENE: My Chinese name?

01:04:17.630 --> 01:04:23.940
So, my Chinese name is- My American name is
a transliteration of my Chinese name, meaning

01:04:23.940 --> 01:04:27.720
my parents picked my American name because
it sounded kind of like my Chinese name.

01:04:27.720 --> 01:04:31.110
My American name is Gene Luen Yang.

01:04:31.110 --> 01:04:34.420
My Chinese name is Yang Ging Luen.

01:04:34.420 --> 01:04:40.860
Now that middle character, Ging, has an interesting
story behind it.

01:04:40.860 --> 01:04:47.410
It's a Chinese tradition to give the gift
of gold to babies when they're first born.

01:04:47.410 --> 01:04:51.410
When I was first born, I got all this gold
from my relatives.

01:04:51.410 --> 01:04:55.500
Then after I became an adult, my mom gave
me this gold.

01:04:55.500 --> 01:04:59.170
When I got this gold as an adult, I looked
through it and on one of these little plates,

01:04:59.170 --> 01:05:00.170
it had my name.

01:05:00.170 --> 01:05:04.680
It had Yang Ging Luen, but the middle character,
Ging, was a different character.

01:05:04.680 --> 01:05:07.070
It sounded the same, but it was a totally
different word.

01:05:07.070 --> 01:05:11.420
I was like, my aunt who gave this to me, she
didn't even know my name.

01:05:11.420 --> 01:05:13.680
She got my name wrong.

01:05:13.680 --> 01:05:14.680
My mom said, "No.

01:05:14.680 --> 01:05:16.320
She didn't get it wrong.

01:05:16.320 --> 01:05:18.360
That was your actual name when you were first
born."

01:05:18.360 --> 01:05:19.710
I said, "Okay, so what does this Ging mean?"

01:05:19.710 --> 01:05:23.320
She says, "That Ging means splendid."

01:05:23.320 --> 01:05:25.810
I said, "It means splendid?

01:05:25.810 --> 01:05:26.810
You name me Splendid?

01:05:26.810 --> 01:05:27.920
Why did you change that?"

01:05:27.920 --> 01:05:33.710
She said, "Well after you turned one and you
started walking around, you kept hitting your

01:05:33.710 --> 01:05:36.210
head.

01:05:36.210 --> 01:05:40.000
We changed it to another Ging, which means
careful."

01:05:40.000 --> 01:05:44.430
That's what my name means now in Chinese.

01:05:44.430 --> 01:05:46.410
It means careful.

01:05:46.410 --> 01:05:47.410
Yes?

01:05:47.410 --> 01:05:50.260
AUDIENCE: How many comics have you made since
you started?

01:05:50.260 --> 01:05:53.610
GENE: So, the question is, how many comics
have I made since I started?

01:05:53.610 --> 01:05:55.470
I have made a lot.

